{
  "stem": "5639.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And sometime in August, I think, the labor camp was liquidated and the majority were sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was among the people who were sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Auschwitz experience belongs to a totally different sphere of experiences.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "To me it is so bizarre and so different from the previous-- already previous-- war and persecution experiences, that I cannot address it as-- how should I say, I cannot address it as freely.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My arrival to Auschwitz was an end of a certain period in my life forever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The arrival in Auschwitz was a beginning of an experience that stayed with me also forever.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not an experience that could have been-- that can, in my opinion, be put on par with any other experiences during the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Being in the way of, of violence, of torture, of-- perhaps brutalization and dehumanization are the only two words that apply to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The brutalization was more spiritual and emotional than physical.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nothing could be more physical than a stay in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The length of stay in Auschwitz, I don't think it's important.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In my case I think I came in August, and I was in Auschwitz during the uprising which, now we all know, took place on the 8th of October.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I could have been between six weeks to two months in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's the intensity of the experience that marks you, not the duration of the experience.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the intensity occurs immediately.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Immediately we were shocked and we stayed in a state of shock.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I couldn't tell you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were thousands and thousands in our cattle truck were perhaps 100.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You never related to the other people, only to the one with whom you were close, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
